WorkItem.Description:
I have the following code:

```
$output     = $objOutputExcel->getActiveSheet();
$template   = $objTemplateExcel->getActiveSheet();

$output->duplicateStyle($template->getStyle('A1'), 'A1');
$output->duplicateStyle($template->getStyle('A2'), 'A2');
```

The problem is that when the second duplicateStyle() line runs, it applies the style to the A1 row. If I comment out the second duplicateStyle() line, the first works fine. If I comment out the first duplicateStyle(), the second works fine.

I saw [in a stackoverflow post](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/18258318/workaround-for-copying-style-with-phpexcel) in the past where Mark had posted a workaround, but when I look at the code Mark mentions, it looks like the fix is already in place.

Any guidance on this would be appreciated.
